Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(diced) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

If you prefer oven-baking your risotto, preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Use an #ovenproof pan{} and 2p: @boiled water for the risotto{600%ml}, 3p: 900ml, 4p: 1200ml of boiled water.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof pan on medium-high heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken thigh{240%g}, @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}, @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and onion. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until the onion has softened and the lardons are browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly.

Stir in the garlic, then cook until the garlic is fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @risotto rice{175%g} into the pan and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the boiled water for the risotto (see pantry for amount), @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and @chicken stock paste{20%g}. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

For oven-baking, pour in all the water at once and cover with a lid or foil. Bake until the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2} (see ingredients for amount).

In a large #bowl{}, combine a squeeze of lemon juice with the @sugar for the dressing{1%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{40%g}, then toss to coat in the dressing.

When the risotto's ready, remove from the oven. Stir in a knob of @?butter{} (if you have any) and three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Stir in a pinch of lemon zest and squeeze in some lemon juice. Taste and add more salt, pepper or lemon zest and juice if needed.

Serve your chicken, bacon and mushroom risotto between your plates with the rocket salad and remaining cheese.

Enjoy!